{"id": "EUVD-2025-12891", "enisaUuid": "2f1f6b03-aae3-3119-b61a-c60e6bb07aa6", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncxl/region: Fix cxl_region leak, cleanup targets at region delete\n\nWhen a region is deleted any targets that have been previously assigned\nto that region hold references to it. Trigger those references to\ndrop by detaching all targets at unregister_region() time.\n\nOtherwise that region object will leak as userspace has lost the ability\nto detach targets once region sysfs is torn down.", "datePublished": "2025-05-01T15:31:51", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-10T21:30:29", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49893", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0d9e734018d70cecf79e2e4c6082167160a0f13f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/45d9fb4b758b9d602ee7776eb6754b0349946aad"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49893", "GHSA-c2p4-prc5-v3mc"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "17a2ef65-678c-3c57-b5e5-c44b84219b7d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b9686e8c8e39d4072081ef078c04915ee51c8af4 <45d9fb4b758b9d602ee7776eb6754b0349946aad"}, {"id": "2293d362-1c4c-35d9-96d3-9ea731450d3f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.8"}, {"id": "81132b6b-22c4-3636-88c9-ea8420e43fe2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.0"}, {"id": "bf5ac094-887d-3f6d-9507-07c72bde5d5c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "d3c4fcea-594b-31d4-8db4-a71bfe9ef566", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b9686e8c8e39d4072081ef078c04915ee51c8af4 <0d9e734018d70cecf79e2e4c6082167160a0f13f"}, {"id": "f67820fb-6744-3d12-be44-12cca37c29c3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "af2bc3e5-c8b3-31f8-b8b5-3dfadf9ae62e", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}